                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-24T09:24:07.848-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-05-08T09:41:24.629-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Generous parental leave supporting new families"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-24T09:25:03.048-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>For new mothers, fathers, adoptive and foster parents in the U.S., AbbVie offers generous time off to focus on welcoming a new child. And, to ease the transition back to the workplace, new parents can phase back to work on a reduced schedule for up to a full year.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Director Jody Alde, who’s been at AbbVie for nearly 20 years, has leveraged the company’s maternity leave for the birth of all three of her children – and plans to do so again with the new child she has on the way.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“I'm very grateful for the maternity leave benefits at AbbVie. Even compared to several years ago, they’ve gotten better and better. I'm very appreciative of being able to have that time as a family to adjust to a fourth child,” she says.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4>
