                            <container4_copy
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <title
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-24T09:24:07.848-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-05-08T09:41:36.930-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Time away to care for sick loved ones"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-24T09:27:54.582-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>AbbVie support also includes employees’ extended families. Through the company’s caregiver leave program, employees in the U.S. receive up to 4 weeks of paid time off and 8 weeks of unpaid time off to look after not only a spouse or child of any age, but also parents, in-laws, grandparents, grandchildren, and siblings with a serious health condition.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>The caregiver leave benefit supported Monica Swanzy, a senior account consultant at Allergan Aesthetics, when her son was diagnosed with aplastic anemia in 2021.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“He needed blood, platelets, and intravenous immunoglobulin every week to stay alive,” Swanzy explained. Leveraging the benefit, Swanzy was able to take 30 days off work while she stayed at the hospital to care for her son.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“I never thought I would have needed to use the caregiver benefit, but it’s a true gift,” she says.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4_copy>
                            <quote
                                cq:styleIds="[1000000000000,1000000000040]"
                                jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-24T09:28:03.025-05:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-24T09:28:21.083-05:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/quote"
                                attributionName="Monica Swanzy"
                                attributionTitle="Senior Account Consultant, Allergan Aesthetics, an AbbVie company"
                                quote="I never thought I would have needed to use the caregiver benefit, but it's a true gift."
                                quoteType="regular"
                                textSize="h0"/>
                            <container4_copy_copy
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <title
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-24T09:24:07.848-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-05-08T09:41:46.856-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Flexible ways of working to help you balance life and work"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-24T09:28:52.606-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>To attend to family matters such as medical appointments or parent-teacher meetings, a strict 9-to-5 schedule can be challenging. This is one of the many reasons AbbVie employees use flexibility – both in where and when they work.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Employees can use AbbVie’s flexibility to help them manage their work and responsibilities at home. One way is Where We Work, AbbVie’s hybrid work model for office-based employees that provides predictable flexibility without sacrificing in-person collaboration. The hybrid work model typically consists of 3 days in the office and 2 days remote. Other kinds of flexibility, which vary by role, include flex-time, part-time, remote work, job sharing, shift changes, compressed work weeks and more.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Flexibility proved essential for AbbVie director Katie Kalivoda as she was raising her two kids, both of whom have ADHD.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“I had to figure things out with my oldest especially, so I needed flexibility to be able to go to doctor’s appointments and talk to teachers. My manager said to me: ‘I trust you to get the job done, you have whatever flexibility you need.’ To have that stated so clearly to me – I could never repay that,” said Kalivoda.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“AbbVie’s Where We Work model has given me the space to be the type of parent that I want to be. If I need to be in school for an event, I block my calendar. If I need to work, my kids understand. It’s a matter of finding what works for you, and AbbVie has allowed me to do that.”&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-24T09:24:28.534-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-24T09:24:28.534-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-24T09:24:07.848-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-05-08T09:43:19.652-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Flexible ways of working to help you balance life and work"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-24T09:29:19.543-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Whether dealing with the stress of parenting or being a caregiver, grieving the loss of a loved one or improving emotional well-being, employees at AbbVie have a variety of resources to help them with their mental health and well-being. One key program is AbbVie’s Employee Assistance Program (EAP).&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>EAP is a free, confidential counseling service, available 24/7 to employees globally and to anyone in their households. Over one in 10 families have accessed AbbVie’s EAP counseling services in the past year. This includes unlimited access to resources for a range of personal or work-related concerns such as parenting, stress, child/elder care, grief, relationships, and work/career related matters.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <text
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-24T09:29:51.478-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-24T09:30:25.186-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;b>Media Inquiries:&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/b>Name: Lily Fragoso&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;Email:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:sara.weitz@abbvie.com&quot;>lily.fragoso@abbvie.com&lt;/a>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4_copy_copy>
                        </par_12>
